sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1175100
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: BBa_K1175028 pBAD Promoter and SecI pump attached to Composite norvirus antibody BBa_K875004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
These are the three essential parts prtD, prtE, prtF, that make up the Type I secretion system from Erwinia chrysanthemi.This part is made of 3 genes: prtD, prtE, and prtF, that constitute a type I Erwinia chrysanthemi secretion system. The Pump is expressed from a strong constitutive promoter, BBa_k206000, and has the translational terminator BBa_B0014. In pSB1C3.
Used to secrete proteins containing prtB C-terminal tag. The prtB C-terminal tag is built into the protein generator [BBa_K215002]. Any protein of interest can be inserted into the protein generator and then secreted when used in conjunction with this secretion system.
This construct is designed for the expression of an already descibed engeneered antinorovirus (NoV) monoclonal antibody (mAb 54.6) in fusion with LPP-OmpA. The antibody is expressed in a single chain fragment variable (scFv) format containing light (VL) and heavy (VH) variable domains separeted by a flexible peptide linker. It has already been reported that the scFv 54.6 binds a native recombinant NoV particles (VLPs) and inhibits VLP interaction with cells. LPP-OmpA functions as a leader sequence and an anchor to display the scFv ot the bacterial surface.The construct consistes of T5 Lac Operator (Bba_K875002), ribosomal binding site, LPP-OmpA-scFv 54.6 antinorovirus, Histidine tag (6HIS), Terminator (B0015).
The part combines a strongly expressed secretion pump with a antinoroviral antibody that is expressed in the outer-membrane can/will be combined with BBa_K1175012 A composite part formed between BBa_K206000 strong pBAD promoter, BBa_B0034 strong RBS, and BBa_K215001 a purification and secretion tag.
For full characterization data on this part, please see the University of Washington 2009 iGEM project page, Team Trieste iGEM 2012 and, Wisconsin Lutheran College 2013 iGEM project page.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nicholas K. Goldner
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: iGEM parts registry, Team Trieste 2012, University of Washington 2009 and Wisconsin Lutheran College 2013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part is fairly large and must be carefully handled to avoid shearing. It also needs to be added in a much higher molar ration than 1:1:1 closer to 10:10:1 ie Part 1: Part 2: Backbone. This can be done by decreasing the amount of backbone and doubling the ligation volume.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pBAD
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pBAD is an E.coli promoter that is induced by L-arabinose. K206000 is a mutagenized pBAD promoter that is responsive to lower concentrations of arabinose than wild type (I13453) and, additionally, exhibits a higher maximum of protein expression as measured by coupling to a fluorescent reporter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amelia Hardjasa
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence was obtained by applying all mutations that upregulated AraC binding and subsequent promoter activity listed in reference [1].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There were no special design considerations.
